org.barjo.atmosgi
Interface AtmosphereService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AtmosphereComponent
public interface AtmosphereService

OSGi Service which represents an AtmosphereFramework. Thanks to this service you can add AtmosphereHandler and get the BroadcasterFactory at runtime. User: barjo Date: 18/10/12 Time: 11:08

addAtmosphereHandler

void addAtmosphereHandler(String mapping,
                          org.atmosphere.cpr.AtmosphereHandler handler)
Add a new AtmosphereHandler to the framework with the given mapping. Be aware that the mapping is added to the atmosphere root, if the root is /atmosphere, then the handler will be accessible through the /atmosphere/ address.

Parameters:
mapping - The AtmosphereHandler mapping. (e.g /toto)
handler - The AtmosphereHandler to be added.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if an handler is already linked to this mapping.
